      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification must demonstrate solution convergence and correctness against analytical benchmarks for beam bending and contact problems.",
      "rationale": "All three FEA codes verified against Timoshenko beam bending analytical solution and Hertzian contact benchmark. Maximum error 0.8% for beam bending, 1.4% for contact. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate QoI change less than 2% between successive refinements; Richardson extrapolation applied.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (coarse: 42k elements, medium: 118k elements, fine: 347k elements). Richardson extrapolation gives GCI < 0.8% for all three QoIs. Final mesh uses medium density as cost-accuracy optimum. Achieved level exceeds required."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals must converge below 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance verified.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear Newton-Raphson solver converged to residual norm below 1e-8 for all 25 load increments. Energy balance error below 0.01%. Automatic time stepping with bisection confirmed solution path stability."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and loading protocol by analyst not involved in original model development.",
      "rationale": "Model setup independently reviewed by a second FDA analyst. Boundary conditions (fixed inferior vertebral body, load applied at superior body centroid per F1717 geometry) confirmed correct. Material assignments and contact definitions reviewed and approved. No use errors identified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form must capture nonlinear geometric effects and material plasticity; contact formulation must be appropriate for screw-rod and screw-vertebral body interfaces.",
      "rationale": "Large-deformation formulation (NLGEOM ON) employed throughout. Ti-6Al-4V modeled with bilinear isotropic hardening (E=114 GPa, sy=880 MPa, tangent modulus=1.2 GPa) calibrated from coupon tests. Augmented Lagrangian contact with friction coefficient 0.2 applied at all metal-metal interfaces. Model form assessed as adequate for COU."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric parameters must be derived from measurements on the actual test specimens or equivalent production stock; uncertainty quantification required.",
      "rationale": "Geometry imported from production CAD with dimensional verification against CMM measurements (max deviation 0.03 mm). Ti-6Al-4V material properties from 12 coupon specimens machined from same stock as test constructs. Coefficient of variation on yield strength: 1.8%. Parametric sensitivity study confirms QoI uncertainty below 3% for ±2SD material property variation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test specimens required; specimens must be production-representative and traceability to manufacturing lot documented.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-representative components (6 tested at Lab 1, 5 at Lab 2). Lot traceability documented for all screws and rods. No specimens excluded. Sample size meets required level per V&V 40 Table 1 guidance for medium model risk."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must span the range of clinically relevant loading rates and environments; minimum two test conditions required for medium model risk.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min per ASTM F1717) under ambient laboratory conditions. Dynamic loading conditions and physiological temperature were not evaluated. Achieved level (2) is below required level (3); this gap is acknowledged as a limitation of the current validation campaign and is flagged for future work."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs must be demonstrably equivalent to experimental conditions; documented mapping between test setup parameters and FEA boundary conditions required.",
      "rationale": "Formal input equivalency matrix prepared mapping 14 experimental parameters (crosshead displacement rate, fixture geometry, torque applied to set screws, rod diameter, etc.) to corresponding FEA inputs. All parameters mapped with documented justification. No unresolved discrepancies."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) must be computed for all QoIs; acceptance threshold E/uval < 1.96 must be satisfied.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 8 for all three QoIs: stiffness 0.88, yield force 0.74, force at 40 mm 0.32. All values below 1.96 threshold. Comparison area metric also computed for full force-displacement curve; value 0.91 indicates excellent agreement. Acceptance criteria satisfied for all QoIs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs must be directly linked to the clinical performance endpoints and the regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in the 510(k) predicate comparison protocol. All three are mechanically interpretable as proxies for clinical rigidity and fatigue margin. QoI relevance confirmed by clinical biomechanics subject matter expert review."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must replicate the COU geometry, loading mode, and regulatory context; deviations must be justified.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities use the identical non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw geometry and ASTM F1717 test configuration as the COU. Both laboratories are FDA-recognized and operate under ISO 17025 accreditation. The regulatory context (510(k) substantial equivalence) is directly served by this validation campaign. Relevance assessed as fully adequate."
